Key Match Events: Derrick White scored 23 points to lead the Boston Celtics to a 109-86 victory over the Houston Rockets.
Jayson Tatum and Payton Pritchard each added 20 points for the Celtics.
The Celtics scored the first 11 points of the fourth quarter to extend their lead to 93-72.
Kristaps Porzingis returned after missing four games with a sprained left ankle and added 11 points with five rebounds.
Jalen Green scored 27 points for the Rockets.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Boston Celtics played without Jaylen Brown, who missed a second straight game with a shoulder strain.
Houston Rockets started 38-year-old Jeff Green for the first time this season due to Jabari Smith Jr.'s injury.
